02/12/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- The opposition Democratic Party (DP) is seeking the resignation of Finance Minister Kastriot Islami of the Socialist Party -led government. 
At a press conference Sunday (1 December), DP official Edmond Spaho expressed the party's concern over problems with the customs system. 
At issue, data suggesting that projected revenues from customs duties have not materialised for three consecutive months. 
In August, September and October, revenues were at 93 per cent to 97 per cent of projections. 
The loss to the state budget during the third quarter was $20m, where as the loss during the April-November period was $50m. 
(ATA - 01/12/02)
